<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-8357] EncodingGroovyMethods.decodeBase64() throws &quot;bad character in base64 value&quot; when meets \t \r</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8357</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;EncodingGroovyMethods.decodeBase64() throws &quot;bad character in base64 value&quot; RuntimeException when the method meets \t \r character.&lt;br/&gt;
I found in org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.EncodingGroovyMethodsSupport.TRANSLATE_TABLE has a mistake:&lt;br/&gt;
    static final byte[] TRANSLATE_TABLE = (&lt;br/&gt;
            &quot;\u0042\u0042\u0042\u0042\u0042\u0042\u0042\u0042&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
                    //                    &lt;font color=&quot;red&quot;&gt;\t&lt;/font&gt;    &lt;font color=&quot;yellow&quot;&gt;\n&lt;/font&gt;                &lt;font color=&quot;blue&quot;&gt;\r&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                    + &quot;\u0042&lt;font color=&quot;red&quot;&gt;\u0042&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;yellow&quot;&gt;\u0041&lt;/font&gt;\u0041\u0042&lt;font color=&quot;blue&quot;&gt;\u0042&lt;/font&gt;\u0041\u0042&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
I mark them in color.&lt;br/&gt;
I believe it&apos;s an offset mistake.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
